e worst hit by the under-occupation charge and benefit capping.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This was targeted work, as we were aware of who was to be affected; this is not the case with the gradual migration to Universal Credit, and we would welcome discussi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">on on how best to engage tenants for a change which may still be some years off.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  This is especially difficult given the changing timescales for implementation and a concern that national IT systems will not be ready or robust enough to support UC implemen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tation. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The PAG also noted that despite the excellent work done to reduce and manage homelessness as part of the 2012 agenda, we will find it difficult to continue to provide affordable temporary accommodation to those on benefits. Most of the temporary </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">accommodation in Fife is provided by good quality Council owned and managed properties. These properties are provided more cheaply than in other sectors, yet the tenants are penalised because the Supported Exempt Accommodation ruling does not apply. The PA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G supports the extension of SEA to LA properties as we </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">believe this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> provides stability for homeless people and offers best value.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have also tried to mitigate the effects through an increased Discretionary Allowance Payment fund. However, this is not a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sustainable position; tenants cannot increase mobility while there is not affordable housing for them to move to. In Fife, a 2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bedroomed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Council flat is cheaper t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">han a 1 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bedroomed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> private flat, even when such a vacancy can be found.  For many though, espec</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ially parents with access, the new housing support rules work against the Government’s policy of helping fathers maintain links with their children.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The changes mean that, in a climate of reduced resources for developing advice, employability, training, w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e are all having to manage an increased work load whether </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">this be new customers, or existing customers with new issues. The loss of income, despite our best efforts and the use of DHP, mean that fewer new homes can be built in Fife, and the business plans </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for RSLs and the LA are at risk.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">27 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>